<TITLE> Chidambaram admits security lapses over Mumbai </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI,Dec 05(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Palaniappan Chidambaram, India's new home minister, said on Friday there had been security lapses that led to the Mumbai attacks that killed 171 people, but said they would be addressed. "I would be less than truthful if I said there were no lapses. These happens sometimes. These are being looked into," Chidambaram told reporters in Mumbai. "We will address the causes that led to the lapses."
